The article discusses President Donald J. Trump's stance on the Iran nuclear deal, one year after the United States withdrew from the agreement. President Trump criticizes the deal as a "disastrous one-sided deal" that failed to stop Iran's nuclear program and its malign activities. He emphasizes the need for a maximum pressure campaign to address all aspects of Iran's behavior and prevent the development of nuclear weapons. The article calls on the Iranian regime to abandon its nuclear ambitions, change its destructive behavior, respect the rights of its people, and return to negotiations in good faith.